NTA, but the best way to learn how to draw backgrounds (in my unprofessional opinion) is also the really boring way: still lifes.

Composing objects in a 3D space is all a background is, and still lifes with simple objects is the fastest way to figure that out. The simplification comes with time as you get more experience with what level of detail that won't distract from the foreground, at least that's how I started to figure it out.
